value.title: Georgia election guardian Raffensperger faces heat as Trump contests defeat
value.excerpt: Georgia's Republican secretary of state, Brad Raffensperger, cemented his status as an unlikely hero for U.S. Democrats following a fresh clash in which he rejected President Donald Trump's claims that his election defeat was the result of widespread fraud.

value.title: Harris lambasts Trump call with Georgia officials as 'bold abuse of power'
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris slammed President Donald Trump and his call pushing Georgia Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger to "find" votes to overturn the election results, a "bald-faced, bold abuse of power," in Savannah, Georgia, on Sunday.

value.title: Trump to award Medal of Freedom to GOP Reps. Devin Nunes and Jim Jordan
value.excerpt: Before he leaves office, President Donald Trump will award the nation's highest civilian honor to two of his most vocal political allies who defended him throughout his impeachment, Rep. Devin Nunes of California and Rep. Jim Jordan of Ohio, as the White House has been inundated with requests for others,

value.title: Republicans condemn GOP ‘scheme’ to undo election for Trump
value.excerpt: The extraordinary Republican effort to overturn the presidential election was condemned Sunday by an outpouring of current and former GOP officials.

value.title: Kamala Harris' 'Fweedom' story mirrors MLK account
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala D. Harris told a story about her participation as a little girl in a civil rights march that mirrors an account told by the Rev. Martin Luther King.

value.title: Trump urged Georgia election official to 'find' votes in phone call, insisting he won: report
value.excerpt: President Trump insisted that he won the state of Georgia in the 2020 presidential race during a phone call with Georgia’s Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger over the weekend, reportedly urging him to “find” enough votes to reverse the state’s results.

value.title: Audio: Trump berates Ga. secretary of state, urges him to ‘find’ votes
value.excerpt: In a one-hour phone call on Saturday with Georgia election officials, President Trump insisted he won the state and threatened vague legal consequences if the officials did not act. These are excerpts from the call.

value.title: Pence 'welcomes' congressional Republicans' bid to challenge electoral votes
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Saturday signaled his support for a bid by Republicans lawmakers to challenge electoral votes when Congress is expected to certify President-elect Joe Biden's victory in a meeting this week.

value.title: President Trump rails against media coverage of Fauci: ‘He works for me’
value.excerpt: President Trump on Sunday griped that the news media is giving Dr. Anthony Fauci credit for the coronavirus response that he deserves.

value.title: US surgeon general: 'No reason to doubt' Covid-19 death toll number after Trump claims deaths 'exaggerated'
value.excerpt: US Surgeon General Dr. Jerome Adams on Sunday said he has "no reason to doubt" the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's Covid-19 death toll, contradicting President Donald Trump's claim that the agency has "exaggerated" its numbers.

value.title: Trump's allies are rounding on Lin Wood after he tweeted about executing Mike Pence and arresting Mitch McConnell
value.excerpt: Trump lawyer had posted a series of unhinged tweets saying the vice president should be arrested and executed over the 2020 election results.

value.title: Iran's foreign minister urges Trump to avoid Israel 'trap' to provoke war
value.excerpt: Iranian Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif urged U.S. President Donald Trump on Saturday not to be "trapped" by an alleged Israeli plan to provoke a war through attacks on U.S. forces in Iraq.

value.title: Eric Trump, Don Jr. party with Vanilla Ice at Mar-a-Lago New Year’s bash
value.excerpt: President Trump skipped out on performances by ’90s pop-rapper Vanilla Ice, Beach Boys founder Mike Love and other throwback acts at a pricey Mar-a-Lago New Year’s Eve bash.

value.title: Trump urges people to 'get ready to vote' in Georgia just hours after calling the Senate runoff elections 'both illegal and invalid'
value.excerpt: President Trump will attend a rally in Georgia on Monday for Senators Kelly Loeffler and David Perdue.

value.title: On the anniversary eve of the drone strike ordered by Trump that killed its top general, Iran reveals its plan to enrich uranium to 20% purity
value.excerpt: "We are like soldiers and our fingers are on the triggers," the head of Iran's civilian atomic energy organization said.

value.title: Iran foreign minister warns Trump 'fireworks will backfire,' as tensions escalate
value.excerpt: Amid heightened tensions between the U.S. and Iran, Iranian Foreign Minister Javad Zarif on Saturday warned President Trump that any "fireworks would backfire."

value.title: Trump the clear Republican 'front-runner' in next White House race
value.excerpt: There's more than three years to go until the next Iowa caucuses and New Hampshire presidential primary, but what some considered the first cattle call in the 2024 White House race takes place next week.

value.title: Federal judge throws out Gohmert lawsuit asking Pence to interfere in Electoral College count
value.excerpt: A federal judge threw out a lawsuit from Rep. Louie Gohmert of Texas and several Arizona Republicans seeking to force Vice President Mike Pence to help throw the election to President Donald Trump next week when Congress meets to count the Electoral College votes.

value.title: Trump vetoes California fishing bill over seafood trade deficit
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump vetoed a bill to gradually end the use of large-mesh drift gillnets deployed in federal waters off the coast of California.

value.title: Trump urges South Dakota governor to challenge ‘RINO’ Sen. Thune
value.excerpt: Thune, the Senate majority whip, outraged Trump last month when he said a challenge to the Electoral College results would “go down like a shot dog.”

value.title: Pence seeks dismissal of suit aiming to overturn election
value.excerpt: The Justice Department has asked a federal judge to dismiss a last-gasp lawsuit led by a House Republican that seeks to give Vice President Mike Pence the power to overturn the results of the presiden

value.title: What Will Pence Do When Congress Counts the Votes?
value.excerpt: Readers are shocked that the question is being asked and speculate that the vice president may find an excuse not to be present. They also criticize Senator Josh Hawley.

value.title: Mike Pence heading to Georgia on Monday ahead of runoff elections
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is heading to Georgia on Monday to campaign ahead of Tuesday’s critical U.S. Senate runoff elections.

value.excerpt: Guests who paid four-figures for tickets to President Donald Trump's annual New Year's Eve party were left to party with his personal attorney Rudy Giuliani, his two adult sons and various figures from the conservative media — none of whom wore masks — after the President made a last-minute decision

value.title: Fact check: President Trump spent Thanksgiving with troops in Afghanistan in 2019, not 2020
value.excerpt: Social media users having been sharing posts that claim President Donald Trump spent Thanksgiving 2020 with troops in Bagram, Afghanistan, not playing golf. This claim is false: the photo of Trump in Bagram is from 2019.
